  "pr_number": 2831,
  "issue_number": 2830,
  "issue_title": "Mutate/merged permanents over-trigger \"dies\" / \"leaves the battlefield\" (once per component card instead of once)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\nWhen a merged permanent (a creature mutated via the **Mutate** keyword, CR 702.140 / 730) leaves the\nbattlefield, the engine fires \"whenever a creature dies\" / \"whenever ~ leaves the battlefield\"\ntriggers **once per component card** in the pile, instead of **once** for the single permanent. The\n\"creature died this turn\" look-back is over-counted the same way. CR 730.3 says only **one**\npermanent leaves the battlefield, so this over-triggers every death/leave payoff by the size of the\nmutate stack.\n\n## CR reference (verified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`)\n- **CR 730.3:** \"If a merged permanent leaves the battlefield, **one permanent leaves the\n  battlefield** and each of the individual components are put into the appropriate zone.\"\n- **CR 712.21** (the meld analogue of the same \"single object represented by multiple cards\" rule,\n  with an explicit worked example):\n  > \"Chittering Host, a melded permanent, dies. An ability that triggers 'whenever a creature dies'\n  > triggers **once**. An ability that triggers 'whenever a card is put into a graveyard from\n  > anywhere' triggers **twice**.\"\n\nSo the correct behavior is asymmetric:\n- \"dies\" / \"leaves the battlefield\" (battlefield-exit observers) \u2192 fire **once** (one permanent left).\n- \"put into a graveyard from anywhere\" \u2192 fire **once per card** (N cards entered the graveyard).\n\n## Root cause\n`crates/engine/src/game/merge.rs` \u2192 `split_merged_permanent_on_leave` routes each non-survivor\ncomponent to the destination zone through the full `move_to_zone` flow:\n\n```rust\nfor component_id in components {\n    if component_id == merged_id {\n        continue; // survivor rides the normal move_to_zone after this fn\n    }\n    // merge.rs:317\n    crate::game::zones::move_to_zone(state, component_id, dest, events); // emits a battlefield-exit event\n}\n```\n\nEach component has `zone = Battlefield` (set in `merge_object_onto`, `merge.rs:100`), so\n`move_to_zone` takes the normal exit path and pushes\n`GameEvent::ZoneChanged { object_id: <component>, from: Some(Battlefield), to: <dest> }`. The\nsurvivor then emits its own exit event. Result: **N** battlefield-exit events for one departing\npermanent.\n\nThe battlefield-exit observers all key on `from == Some(Battlefield)` with no de-duplication and no\n\"single merged permanent\" guard, so each component matches:\n- `match_leaves_battlefield` (`trigger_matchers.rs:2839`): `if *from != Some(Zone::Battlefield) { return false; }`\n- the \"dies\" form (ChangesZone `Battlefield \u2192 Graveyard`) matches the same way\n- `ParsedCondition::CreatureDiedThisTurn` (`restrictions.rs:1154`): `r.from_zone == Some(Zone::Battlefield)`\n\nEach component is a creature card carrying the controller's characteristics, so each matches\n\"whenever a creature you control dies / leaves the battlefield.\"\n\nConfirmed absent on current main:\n- **No suppression** \u2014 no merge-component trigger guard exists in `trigger_matchers.rs` /\n  `events.rs` / `zones.rs` (the only `merge` references near the matchers are for the separate\n  `Mutated`-event matcher, not a leave/dies suppression).\n- **No test coverage** \u2014 `merge_tests.rs` asserts only that components reach the correct *zone*,\n  never the trigger count.\n\n## Current (wrong) behavior\nA mutate stack of N cards leaving the battlefield fires \"whenever a creature you control dies\" (and\n\"whenever ~ leaves the battlefield\", and the died-this-turn condition) **N times**.\n\n## Correct behavior (CR 730.3 + CR 712.21)\n- Exactly **one** \"dies\" / \"leaves the battlefield\" trigger fires (the single permanent's departure \u2014\n  the survivor's move).\n- \"Whenever a card is put into a graveyard from anywhere\" still fires **once per component card**.\n\n## Concrete scenario\n- You control Blood Artist (\"Whenever a creature dies, target player loses 1 life and you gain 1\n  life\") and a 3-card mutate stack (a creature mutated twice).\n- A board wipe destroys the mutate stack.\n- **Correct:** Blood Artist triggers **once** \u2192 opponent loses 1, you gain 1.\n- **Actual:** Blood Artist triggers **3 times** \u2192 opponent loses 3, you gain 3.\n- The same over-count hits Midnight Reaper (draw N instead of 1), Zulaport Cutthroat, Mayhem Devil,\n  and every aristocrats payoff \u2014 a real life-total and card-advantage swing.\n\n## Fix\nRelocate each non-survivor component to the destination **as a new object** that did not\nindependently leave the battlefield \u2014 emitting `ZoneChanged { from: None, to: dest }` (mirroring\ntoken creation, CR 111.1) \u2014 so battlefield-exit observers (`from == Battlefield`) fire only for the\nsurvivor, while origin-agnostic observers (\"put into a graveyard from anywhere\") still fire once per\ncomponent (CR 712.21).\n\nImplemented in `merge.rs` via a new `put_component_into_zone` helper that composes existing zone\nbuilding blocks instead of `move_to_zone`:\n- snapshots the component's characteristics, then applies `zones::apply_zone_exit_cleanup`\n  (CR 400.7 new-object reset) \u2014 made `pub(crate)` for reuse;\n- adds the component to its **own owner's** destination zone (`zones::add_to_zone`), defensively\n  removing it from the battlefield list first (a no-op under the runtime invariant);\n- preserves descend bookkeeping (nontoken permanent card \u2192 graveyard);\n- builds the `ZoneChangeRecord` with `from: None` and feeds it to `restrictions::record_zone_change`,\n  so the `CreatureDiedThisTurn` look-back is consistent with the event;\n- token components are still removed by SBA (CR 111.7) after entering the new zone.\n\nThe survivor continues to ride the normal `move_to_zone` flow, providing the single legitimate\nbattlefield-exit event.\n\n### Files changed\n- `crates/engine/src/game/merge.rs` \u2014 new `put_component_into_zone` helper; split loop calls it.\n- `crates/engine/src/game/zones.rs` \u2014 `apply_zone_exit_cleanup` made `pub(crate)` (visibility only).\n- `crates/engine/src/game/merge_tests.rs` \u2014 regression tests + event-counting helpers.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [x] A 3-component mutate stack leaving the battlefield emits **exactly one** battlefield-exit event\n      (`from == Battlefield`), so \"whenever a creature dies / leaves the battlefield\" fires once.\n- [x] \"Whenever a card is put into a graveyard from anywhere\" still fires **once per component card**\n      (every component produces a `to == Graveyard` zone change) \u2014 CR 712.21.\n- [x] The single-exit invariant holds regardless of pile size (2- and 3-component tests).\n- [x] No regression on the existing `merge_tests.rs` zone-routing assertions.\n\n## Verification\n- `cargo fmt --all --check` \u2014 clean.\n- `cargo clippy -p engine --all-targets` \u2014 0 warnings/errors.\n- `cargo test -p engine --lib game::merge_tests` \u2014 18/18 pass (incl. the 2 new regression tests).\n- `cargo test -p engine --lib` \u2014 11231 passed; the only 3 failures are a **pre-existing, unrelated**\n  card-data \u2194 code mismatch (`unknown variant SourceIsRenowned` during card-data deserialization in\n  `*_db_load_path` tests), independent of this change.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-10T20:21:31.000Z",
